comments.body:
@nikic
Understood, and what you are suggesting makes perfect sense. I have created a new PR that applies the change being discussed (#181267). It's draft for now until we complete some internal testing to get confidence that it will not be detrimental to any AMDGPU users. However, I think if we are going to do this globally we need buy-in from owners of other targets to make sure they are on-board with such a change. This may mean collaborating on performance testing. If possible, can you please suggest specific people from different organizations (who would represent the different targets) to include on the new PR for their buy-in?

In case a global change doesn't get all the buy-in needed, I have also prepared a second PR that will only apply this change for AMDGPU. (#181241)
